newsitem.title: JORDAN: Jordan overnight rates rise to 8.00-8.50 percent.
newsitem.headline: Jordan overnight rates rise to 8.00-8.50 percent.

text.p: Jordan overnight dinar rates rose to a 8.00-8.50 percent range on Wednesday from 7.75-8.00 percent on Tuesday as the market continued to be squeezed for cash, dealers said.
A tight market has persisted since start of weekly trade on Saturday after many banks tied up funds in the last 15 million dinar CD (certificate of deposit) auction, bankers said.
Excess liquidity sent rates tumbling to a low 3.00 percent average last week.
